SB9 Enrolled
1 Enrolled, An Act,
2
3
4 Relating to the Alabama Clean Indoor Air Act, to amend
5 Sections 22-15A-1 and 22-15A-3, Code of Alabama 1975, to
6 rename the act the Vivian Davis Figures Clean Indoor Air Act;
7 and to prohibit the smoking of electronic nicotine delivery
8 systems in the same manner as the smoking of tobacco products
9 is prohibited.
10 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
11 Section 1. Sections 22-15A-1 and 22-15A-3 of the Code
12 of Alabama 1975, are amended to read as follows:
13 "§22-15A-1
14 This chapter shall be known and may be cited as the
15 "Alabama Vivian Davis Figures and Barbara Drummond Clean
16 Indoor Air Act.""
17 "§22-15A-3
18 As used in this chapter, the following words and
19 phrases shall have the following meanings:
20 (1) BAR AND LOUNGE. Any establishment which is
21 primarily devoted to the serving of alcoholic beverages for
22 consumption by patrons on the premises and in which the
23 serving of food is only incidental to the consumption of
24 beverages. Although a restaurant may contain a bar, the term
25 "bar" shall not include the restaurant dining area.
26 (2) CHILD CARE FACILITY. Any facility caring for
27 children.
28 (3) DEPARTMENT. The Alabama Department of Public
Page 1

(3) DEPARTMENT. The Alabama Department of Public
SB9 Enrolled
29 Health.
30 (4) EMPLOYER. Any person, partnership, association,
31 corporation, or nonprofit entity that employs five or more
32 persons, including the legislative, executive, and judicial
33 branches of state government; and any county, city, town, or
34 village, or any other political subdivision of the state; any
35 public authority, commission, agency, or public benefit
36 corporation; or any other separate corporate instrumentality
37 or unit of state or local government.
38 (5) GOVERNMENT BUILDING. Any building owned or operated
39 by the state, including the legislative, executive, and
40 judicial branches of state government; any county, city, town,
41 or village, or any other political subdivision of the state;
42 any public authority, commission, agency, or public benefit
43 corporation; or any other separate corporate instrumentality
44 or unit of state or local government.
45 (6) PUBLIC CONVEYANCE. A bus, taxi, train, trolley,
46 boat, and any other means of public transit.
47 (7) PUBLIC MEETING. Any meeting open to the public
48 unless held in a private residence.
49 (8) PUBLIC PLACE. Any enclosed area to which the public
50 is permitted, including, but not limited to, auditoriums,
51 elevators, hospitals, nursing homes, libraries, courtrooms,
52 jury waiting rooms and deliberation rooms, theatres theaters,
53 museums, common areas of retirement homes, restaurants,
54 laundromats, health facilities, educational facilities,
55 shopping malls, government buildings, sports and recreational
56 facilities, places of employment, airports, banks, retail
Page 2

facilities, places of employment, airports, banks, retail
SB9 Enrolled
57 stores, and service establishments. A private residence is not
58 a "public place."
59 (9) SERVICE LINE. Any indoor line at which one or more
60 persons are waiting for or receiving service of any kind,
61 whether or not the service involves the exchange of money.
62 (10) SMOKING. The burning of a lighted cigarette,
63 cigar, pipe, or any other matter or substance that contains
64 tobacco, and the use of an electronic nicotine delivery system
65 as defined in Section 28-11-2.
66 (11) SMOKING AREA. Any designated area meeting the
67 requirements of Section 22-15A-7."
68 Section 2. This act shall become effective on October
69 1, 2026.
